message.content:
They had been married for six years, but the salary raise, on the expectation of which they had done so, had not materialised. "Do you know I had to send back our bedroom furniture in the second year," she moaned. She had contacts in political circles, a school-friend of hers having married Lester Peron, a liberal senator with a seat on the (Literally) all-powerful Rocket Release Board.

Haskelfiles
